msgid "Chapter 8: Container Snapshots"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/lxd_server/08-snapshots.md:15
msgid ""
"Throughout this chapter you will need to execute commands as your "
"unprivileged user (\"lxdadmin\" if you've been following along from the "
"beginning of this book)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/lxd_server/08-snapshots.md:17
msgid ""
"Container snapshots, along with a snapshot server (which we will get to more "
"later), are probably the most important aspect of running a production LXD "
"server. Snapshots ensure quick recovery, and can be used for safety when you "
"are, say, updating the primary software that runs on a particular container. "
"If something happens during the update that breaks that application, you "
"simply restore the snapshot and you are back up and running with only a few "
"seconds worth of downtime."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/lxd_server/08-snapshots.md:19
msgid ""
"The author used LXD containers for PowerDNS public facing servers, and the "
"process of updating those applications became so much more worry-free, since "
"you can snapshot the container first before continuing."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/lxd_server/08-snapshots.md:21
msgid "You can even snapshot a container while it is running."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../src/docs/books/lxd_server/08-snapshots.md:22
#, no-wrap
msgid "The snapshot process"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/lxd_server/08-snapshots.md:25
msgid ""
"We'll start by getting a snapshot of the ubuntu-test container by using this "
"command:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/books/lxd_server/08-snapshots.md:26
#, no-wrap
msgid "lxc snapshot ubuntu-test ubuntu-test-1\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/lxd_server/08-snapshots.md:31
msgid ""
"Here, we are calling the snapshot \"ubuntu-test-1\", but it can be called "
"anything you like. To make sure that you have the snapshot, do an \"lxc info"
"\" of the container:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/books/lxd_server/08-snapshots.md:32
#, no-wrap
msgid "lxc info ubuntu-test\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/lxd_server/08-snapshots.md:37
msgid ""
"We've looked at an info screen already, so if you scroll to the bottom, you "
"should see:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/books/lxd_server/08-snapshots.md:38
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Snapshots:\n"
"  ubuntu-test-1 (taken at 2021/04/29 15:57 UTC) (stateless)\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/lxd_server/08-snapshots.md:44
msgid "Success! Our snapshot is in place."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/lxd_server/08-snapshots.md:46
msgid "Now, get into the ubuntu-test container:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/books/lxd_server/08-snapshots.md:47
#, no-wrap
msgid "lxc exec ubuntu-test bash\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/lxd_server/08-snapshots.md:52
msgid "And create an empty file with the _touch_ command:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/books/lxd_server/08-snapshots.md:53
#, no-wrap
msgid "touch this_file.txt\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/lxd_server/08-snapshots.md:58
msgid "Now exit the container."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/lxd_server/08-snapshots.md:60
msgid ""
"Before we restore the container as it was prior to creating the file, the "
"safest way to restore a container, particularly if there have been a lot of "
"changes, is to stop it first:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/books/lxd_server/08-snapshots.md:61
#, no-wrap
msgid "lxc stop ubuntu-test\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/lxd_server/08-snapshots.md:66
msgid "Then restore it:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/books/lxd_server/08-snapshots.md:67
#, no-wrap
msgid "lxc restore ubuntu-test ubuntu-test-1\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/lxd_server/08-snapshots.md:72
msgid "Then start the container again:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/books/lxd_server/08-snapshots.md:73
#, no-wrap
msgid "lxc start ubuntu-test\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/lxd_server/08-snapshots.md:78
msgid ""
"If you get back into the container again and look, our \"this_file.txt\" "
"that we created is now gone."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/lxd_server/08-snapshots.md:80
msgid "Once you don't need a snapshot anymore, you can delete it:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block
#: ../src/docs/books/lxd_server/08-snapshots.md:81
#, no-wrap
msgid "lxc delete ubuntu-test/ubuntu-test-1\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/lxd_server/08-snapshots.md:86
msgid "!!! warning"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/lxd_server/08-snapshots.md:88
#, no-wrap
msgid "    You should always delete snapshots with the container running. Why? Well the _lxc delete_ command also works to delete the entire container. If we had accidentally hit enter after \"ubuntu-test\" in the command above, AND, if the container was stopped, the container would be deleted. No warning is given, it simply does what you ask.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/lxd_server/08-snapshots.md:90
#, no-wrap
msgid "    If the container is running, however, you will get this message:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/lxd_server/08-snapshots.md:94
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    ```\n"
"    Error: The instance is currently running, stop it first or pass --force\n"
"    ```\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/lxd_server/08-snapshots.md:96
#, no-wrap
msgid "    So always delete snapshots with the container running.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/lxd_server/08-snapshots.md:97
msgid ""
"The process of creating snapshots automatically, setting expiration of the "
"snapshot so that it goes away after a certain length of time, and auto "
"refreshing the snapshots to the snapshot server will be covered in detail in "
"the following chapters."
msgstr ""
